If your PC has 8GB RAM, Virtual RAM or Swap is the memory which is activated when 8GB is used to prevent application from crashing. 

For eg. it's 4GB, PC will use additional 4GB space (from the hard Drive or SSD). This is called Virutual Memory / Swap / Paging File.
The default size is 4GB. If you wish to increase it, follow the instructions given ahead.
